  "text": "Activated macrophages produce various cytokines, chemokines, and enzymes [CITATION_1] , and exhibit diverse and opposing functions, including pro-and anti-inflammatory responses, tissue repair and destruction, and tumoricidal, proangiogenesis and pro-tumoral functions [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] . The paradoxical plasticity of macrophage function is closely related to the polarized activation state.",
